type: scenario
name: kaijo/ssh-disconnect-abuse-pfsense
description: >
  Detects SSH disconnect-abuse patterns on pfSense systems, where attackers
  repeatedly trigger disconnect events to probe server behavior or evade
  authentication-based detection. Designed for FreeBSD/OpenSSH logs.

author: kaijo
license: MIT
version: 0.1.6

labels:
  service: sshd
  platform: pfSense
  attack_type: disconnect_abuse

tags:
  - pfSense
  - SSH
  - Security
  - Abuse
  - FreeBSD

events:
  - connection_closed
  - disconnect
